The prescription drug cleats, thought to have some effect on pneumonia, is in disarray, slipping out of its prescription and circulating.

3338 words, 7.5 minutes to read

"The family needs it. Can you sell me cleats? "

Another message from the families of those infected with COVID-19 was sent to Birch's mobile phone.

For those infected with AIDS, cleats is no stranger. As an AIDS drug, cleats and other anti-hiv drugs used together, can effectively inhibit virus replication.

In the case of the 2020 pneumonia outbreak, the COVID-19 said it could be used on a trial basis because several experts had suggested that the drug might be effective against the disease, and the National Treatment Plan said it could be tried, more than 20 years old, the antiviral drug has its own bloom moment.

The topic that anti-hiv drugs can treat new coronary pneumonia has been trending on Weibo. Micro-blog, post bar and even fish, there are pneumonia patients'families for medicine information.

This is the fifth person to find Birch.

Before this, Hubei Wuhan, Xiangyang, Shenzhen, Shanghai, Xi'an Internet users have found the head of the AIDS Public Welfare Organization, for the families of infected COVID-19 for a box of "antidote. ".

But he refused all requests for help. "Don't overthink it. "

So far, evidence based medical data have not supported the surprising success of Kleenex in treating COVID-19 pneumonia.

Seek medicine

"who still has cleats, bestie mother pneumonia is serious, need this kind of medicine. " End In micro-blog emergency help.

As of 2400 hours on January 28th, 5,974 people had been infected in the epidemic sweeping the country, including the mother of the last friend. After the diagnosis, my friend's mother was hospitalized at Wuhan No. 7 Hospital, one of the city's designated hospitals for COVID-19 pneumonia patients.

But there's a shortage of Kleenex at the hospital. "Now all have no medicine, get ill want oneself to think of a way to save. " She has some incapability.

And the end of the end of the same urgent family there are many, AIDS public organizations, posted it, in all the channels they can think of, strive to help.

A few days ago, the AIDS Public Welfare Organization Bai Hualin Wechat public accounts in the background message, the frequency of COVID-19, cleats increased significantly, which made Betula Platyphylla feel somewhat abnormal. Not long after, a family member of a COVID-19 patient came to him and asked for cleats.

He realized that the social level of desire for cleats.

"All three of us are infected, please help us, can you buy? " The patient's help message flooded into the "squirrel brother" micro-blog.

He's a temporary pit stop for cleats. His hands around the AIDS people donated 40 boxes of Kleenex, as well as several patients raised funds to buy 220 boxes of imitation Indian Kleenex, will be shipped to the country. That's enough for 300 people. He was commissioned by his fellow patients to donate the drugs to needy COVID-19 patients.

After the donation information was published on Weibo, many people infected with pneumonia sought it out and spent heavily to buy it. "Not for sale, free with a diagnosis and a prescription, " he said, setting limits on donations: a confirmed diagnosis, treatment including Kleenex, and no drugs at his hospital.

"Can you sell me some? I am from Wuhan, the old man in my family got coronavirus pneumonia and could not be admitted to the hospital. Now I can only save myself. I heard on the Internet that cleats might be effective. I want to try. Would you please help a helpless child like me?"On the AIDS Patch, a netizen sent a plea to the drug agent who claimed to have source of Kleenex.

"take two bottles of Kleenex. " In the HIV paste bar, netizen "idle fish have a dream" is also looking for a fever friend medicine. His friend did not meet the conditions of admission to the hospital, at home observation, want to buy cleats treatment. The netizen advised him, "could not be to see the AIDS drug can treat pneumonia that, the drug can not be taken arbitrarily, the body is very harmful. "

And some people want to buy some Kleenex to prevent infection. To this part of the help, "Squirrel" does not pay attention.

There has been a rumor that AIDS in the pneumonia epidemic in the absence of infection. White Birch does not think so, Wuhan has an AIDS patient friend in the hospital through the lung CT found left lung infection, but has not yet been confirmed.

Public Welfare Organization volunteers old four also some can not bear to see, these people treat the medicine as the clothes on Taobao, buy the person who is desperate to cast the doctor, sell the person want the money not to die.

Amid the chaos, prescription drug cleats are flowing out of the prescription.

An accident

The unexpected popularity of cleats was unexpected.

Cleats are Protease inhibitor and contain the main ingredients, Lopinavir and Ritonavir. The two components work together to reduce HIV load by allowing the virus to replicate in non-regenerative, immature forms of HIV particles.

As a free AIDS drug, AIDS infected from the local disease control departments or designated treatment hospitals to receive free. White Birch told reporters, cleats belong to the second-line anti-hiv drug program, not the mainstream drug. Although compared with other anti-hiv drugs, cleats is not prone to drug resistance, but may appear hyperlipidemia, diarrhea and other side effects, so is not favored by AIDS friends.

After several days of panic buying, more than on behalf of the purchase of existing stock has been sold out. A Daigou told reporters that only from New Delhi, India, direct mail replica version of the Kleenex, selling for 850 yuan a box, five to seven days to arrive.

Someone's selling it at a higher price. "Do you know how much they sell for at most? $4,000 a box! " It made Betula Platyphylla very angry.

"If the antiviral is a Harem, then, cleats should be the most senior, has been lukewarm, also not pet a concubine, suddenly suddenly suddenly hit back when the Queen. " "Squirrel Brother" in the circle of friends.

But it's not untraceable.

On Jan. 23, a member of the COVID-19's national expert team, Peking University First Hospital, the head of the Department of respiratory and critical care medicine, Wang Guangfa, told the media, an anti-hiv drug called Lopinavir / Litteau was very effective against him.

Wang Guangfa's reference to "Ropinavir / Litteau Na Wei tablets" is cleats. Since then, the news has spread that AIDS drugs can treat COVID-19 pneumonia.

The same message is coming out of Shanghai.

The Shanghai Municipal Clinical Center for Public Health is one of the city's designated medical facilities for patients with COVID-19 pneumonia, where most of the confirmed cases are treated. On January 24, Lu Hongzhou, the Party secretary of the center, told the outside world that, "We started with the first patient with an anti-aids drug like Klebsiella, and so far, there has been some success, but more clinical observations are needed. "

Xiaoyan, the host of the HIV Post Bar, clearly remembers that the first help-seeking message appeared in the post bar on January 24. He deleted it soon after he found out. Subsequently, there have been a number of buy cleats post, and Daigou travel between, take the opportunity to promote.

He's deleted most of the requests and banned the offending ids. He has his own reasons for deleting the posts. Kleenex is a national free drug and can not be used in circulation. Moreover, as a prescription drug, Kleenex must be bought and used with a doctor's prescription, if we use it rashly, it could cause acute pancreatitis.

At times of high stress, any hint of trouble can lead to unexpected butterfly effect.

On the morning of January 29, the Wuhan Virus Institute of the Chinese Academy of Sciences issued a message saying that three older drugs, including a component of cleats, Litteau, had an inhibitory effect on COVID-19 at the cellular level.

Soon after, Birch received a message from a volunteer asking for medicine: Are there any of these drugs? A netizen in Wuhan was infected and wanted to buy it. The drug seeker attached a screenshot of a media report of the latest discovery by the Wuhan Virus Institute.

Birch understands the panic. However, he advised that suspected infected people must visit a regular hospital and according to the doctor's advice medication. After all, cleats is a prescription drug, but also has certain side effects, after taking regular follow-up, did not take people do not take drugs without authorization.

Curative Effect

At the end of the day, I got a five-day supply of Kleenex. But failed to prevent the friend's mother's condition, high fever does not subside, the spirit is also getting worse.

In theory, COVID-19 and HIV ARE RNA viruses. The proteases of both viruses are similar, so Protease inhibitor might work for both.

Reporters found that in the National Health Commission issued a continuous COVID-19 pneumonia diagnosis and treatment plan, said "antiviral treatment can be tried Lopinavir Ritonavir (200 mg / 50 mg, each time)2 tablets twice a day. "

According to this interpretation of the outside world, cleats is the country's recommended drug. But a trial is not a recommendation.

Li Taisheng, director of the Department of Infectious Diseases of the Chinese Medical Association and chairman-designate of the Peking Union Medical College Hospital, is an expert in the field of AIDS treatment, he was on the fence about the effect of Kleenex on COVID-19 pneumonia.

There is no evidence based medicine to back up COVID-19, who has been hailed as a god in therapy.

Li Taisheng was involved in the prevention and control of SARS. The drug was developed 20 years ago, he recalls, so it was tried during the SARS and Mers outbreaks, but the evidence was inconclusive.

"At the time, there were seven articles that showed no effect, only a retrospective study that said it might be effective. So overall, there's no hard evidence yet, " Li said, although the drug is recommended in national guidelines, the timing and effectiveness of the treatment need to be confirmed clinically.

Wuhan University south-central Hospital Infection Professor, well-known AIDS prevention and treatment experts Gui Xien also reservations. He believes that there is no specific treatment for COVID-19 infection, treatment based on comprehensive treatment, but speculates that effective drugs against other RNA viruses may be effective against the disease, such as cleats. However, its efficacy and safety, appropriate dosage, course of treatment and possible mechanism of action have yet to be explored.

"there is no need, " he said bluntly, for healthy people to buy COVID-19 for prevention

He told reporters that clinical experts in Wuhan have already started a comparative study of Kleenex.
